==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: electrocution
<hw>electrocution</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>execution by
electricity.</def> <note>Electrocution as a form of punishment for crime
is usually carried out while the victim is sitting in a chair specially
designed for the purpose, called an <uses>electric chair</uses>, fitted
with electrodes that contact the head and limbs. To be executed in such
a manner is sometimes referred to in grim humor as to <er>ride the
lightning</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> burning.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>killing by electric shock.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>electrocutioner</ent>⟦br⟧
